		description: "This lute looks and sounds just like a banjo. While on my person, I speak Bullywug. If played unattuned, DC 15 Wis save or 2d4 Psychic. Action to play & cast 1 of 7 spells (see spell sheet). Each can be cast once per dawn using my spellcasting ability & save DC. Play the lute while casting a charm spell with somatic or material components & I can impose disadv. on the save.",
		descriptionLong: "This instrument is, for all intents and purposes, a lute, but looks and sounds like a banjo. While it's on my person, I can speak and understand Bullywug. If I play without attuning, I must pass a DC 15 Wis save or take 2d4 psychic dmg. As an action, I can play the lute & cast 1 of 7 spells: Fly, Invisibility, Levitate, Protection from Evil and Good, Animal Friendship, Protection from Energy (fire only), and Protection from Poison. Each can be cast once per dawn using my spellcasting ability & save DC. If I play the lute while casting a charm effect spell, I can impose disadvantage on the save if the spell has somatic or material components.",
