		description : "The intricate carvings on this polished duskwood wand contain seemingly endless detail. The symbol of the Turning Key — a famous but long-defunct Tavilar adventuring company - is carved on its base. While holding the wand, I occasionally hear female voices whispering encouragement & support. The wand has 3 charges. I can expend 1 charge as an action, & if a secret door or trap is within 30 ft, the wand pulses & points at the nearest one. It regains 1d3 charges at dawn.",
